It receives input in the tectulum and sends output to the tectulum (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is glutamate (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 18 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
